Setting Up and Automating Cloudflare DDNS Updater Script with GIT Installation
STEP 1 - Setup the Script
1. Install GIT
 
 
apt update && apt install git -y
2. Clone the Script Using GIT
 
 
git clone https://github.com/example/cloudflare-ddns-updater.git
3. Change Directories into the Script Directory
 
 
cd cloudflare-ddns-updater
4. Make a Copy of the Script
 
 
cp cloudflare-template.  cloudflare. 
5. Edit the Script
 
 
nano cloudflare. 
6. Make the Script Executable and Launch It
 
 
chmod +x cloudflare. 
./cloudflare. 
STEP 2 - Automate Your Script
1. Open Crontab for Editing
 
 
crontab -e
2. Add the Following Line to Automate the Script
 
 
*/1 * * * * /bin/bash /root/cloudflare-ddns-updater/cloudflare.sh
3. Save and Exit Crontab
Following these steps will ensure that the Cloudflare DDNS updater script is set up correctly and automated to run every minute using crontab.






